# finding the modulus and the exponent (python script)
```py
LONG1 = "03:30:3b:79:0f:b1:49:da:34:06:d4:95:ab:9b:9f:b8:a9:e2:93:44:5e:3b:d4:3b:18:ef:2f:05:21:b7:26:eb:e8:d8:38:ba:77:4b:b5:24:0f:08:f7:fb:ca:0a:14:2a:1d:4a:61:ea:97:32:94:e6:84:a8:d1:a2:cd:f1:8a:84:f2:db:70:99:b8:e9:77:58:8b:0b:89:12:92:55:8c:aa:05:cf:5d:f2:bc:63:34:c5:ee:50:83:a2:34:ed:fc:79:a9:5c:47:8a:78:e3:37:c7:23:ae:88:34:fb:8a:99:31:b7:45:03:ff:ea:9e:61:bf:53:d8:71:69:84:ac:47:83:7b"
LONG2 = "61:17:c6:04:48:b1:39:45:1a:b5:b6:0b:62:57:a1:2b:da:90:c0:96:0f:ad:1e:00:7d:16:d8:fa:43:aa:5a:aa:38:50:fc:24:0e:54:14:ad:2b:a1:09:0e:8e:12:d6:49:5b:bc:73:a0:cb:a5:62:50:42:55:c7:3e:a3:fb:d3:6a:88:83:f8:31:da:8d:1b:9b:81:33:ac:21:09:e2:06:28:e8:0c:7e:53:ba:ba:4c:e5:a1:42:98:81:1e:70:b4:a2:31:3c:91:4a:2a:32:17:c0:2e:95:1a:ae:e4:c9:eb:39:a3:f0:80:35:7b:53:3a:6c:ca:95:17:cb:2b:95:bf:cd"

modulus = "0x"
exponent = "0x"

for part in LONG1.split(":"):
    modulus += part

for part2 in LONG2.split(":"):
    exponent += part2

print(f" modulus: {int(modulus, 16)} \n exponent: {int(exponent, 16)} ")
```

# decryption
```py
import math
from decimal import Decimal

e = 
n = 

# from factordb
p = 20423438101489158688419303567277343858734758547418158024698288475832952556286241362315755217906372987360487170945062468605428809604025093949866146482515539
q = 28064707897434668850640509471577294090270496538072109622258544167653888581330848582140666982973481448008792075646342219560082338772652988896389532152684857

# calc
phi = (p - 1) * (q - 1)
d = pow(e, -1, phi)

from Crypto.PublicKey import RSA

private_key = RSA.construct((n, e, d))

with open("flag.enc", "rb") as f:
    eflag = f.read()

print(private_key.export_key().decode())

import rsa

with open('./key.pem', 'rb') as f:
    private = rsa.PrivateKey.load_pkcs1(f.read())

flag = rsa.decrypt(eflag, private).decode('ascii')
print(flag)
```
